headline: New England Journal of Medicine Publishes Phase 3 ASCENT-04/KEYNOTE-D19 Results Supporting Trodelvy® Plus Keytruda® as a Potential New Standard of Care in First-line PD-L1+ Metastatic Triple-negative Breast Cancer
summary: FOSTER CITY, Calif., January 21, 2026--Gilead Sciences, Inc. (Nasdaq: GILD) today announced The New England Journal of Medicine (NEJM) published the full results from the positive Phase 3 ASCENT-04/KEYNOTE-D19 study evaluating the combination of Trodelvy® (sacituzumab govitecan-hziy) plus Keytruda® (pembrolizumab) in first-line PD-L1+ (CPS ≥10) metastatic triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC).
